# Money and Ledger

- No floating point arithmetic for monetary values, odds, rates, balances, or PnL.
- Money operations must use Decimal utilities.
- Ledger entries are append-only.
- Balance-changing operations require idempotency keys.
- Every exchange, deposit, withdrawal, game bet, trading position, and reward must store a rate snapshot when applicable.
- Available and locked balances must be explicit.
